{
  "text": "Transfection of siRNA. siRNA-NRP1 and a non-sense siRNA (siRNA-CONT) were purchased from Dharmacon (Munich, Germany). The sequences have been selected according to a recent publication [CITATION_1] . A second set of siRNA-NRP1 purchased from Dharmacon as a so-called On-Target plus SMARTpool for NRP1 with defined sequences was used as a control siRNA. Transfection was performed in 6-well plates using 100 pmol siRNA-CONT or siRNA-NRP1 and 5 \u03bcl Lipofectamine 2000 (Invitrogen) in OptiMEM (Invitrogen) according to the manufacturer's instructions. Cells were assayed for alterations in expression levels 2 days post transfection after they were ruptured with PBS and three freeze-thaw cycles. Protein concentration was determined using the DC protein assay (Bio-Rad) and 100 \u03bcg whole protein was analyzed by Western blot. Transfection efficiency was analyzed by transfection of siRNA-GFP (Block-It Fluorescent Oigo, Invitrogen) followed by fluorescence microscopy. Gene knock-down was demonstrated by RT-PCR and Western blot of NRP1 as described above.",
